    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-06T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-06T20:00:00-05:00" n="135"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.6363/266: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-06T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 6, 1942—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 7—12:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1643. Chilean Government has just chartered Argentine tanker <hi rend="italic"
                        >Juncal</hi> believed to be en route to the United States with vegetable oil
                    for Commodity Credit Corporation, for single trip from West Coast United States
                    to Chile with 10 million liters gasoline. This gasoline is ostensibly to
                    increase reserves of Ministry for Defense but when asked whether it would be
                    counted as delivery by pool answer was evasive and there will be nothing to
                    prevent its use for civilian consumption.</p>
                <p>Embassy is also informed that Ministry of Defense has contracted to buy outside
                    of the pool 10,000 barrels of aviation gasoline in steel drums to be delivered
                    within 90 days probably at San Pedro.</p>
                <p>Both transactions will result in considerably higher cost than pool deliveries
                    and Embassy considers them extremely questionable. Local Standard subsidiary has
                    informed headquarters and recommended that the Department investigate
                    immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
